EDIT: after looking at the repro, this may not be a duplicate. Could be a bug in our `UITextInput.deleteBackward`. But we are currently using `rangeOfComposedCharacterSequenceAtIndex` which should delete the entire grapheme cluster.

```objc
NSRange RangeForCharacterAtIndex(NSString* text, NSUInteger index) {
  if (text == nil || index > text.length) {
    return NSMakeRange(NSNotFound, 0);
  }
  if (index < text.length) {
    return [text rangeOfComposedCharacterSequenceAtIndex:index];
  }
  return NSMakeRange(index, 0);
}
```
